UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ShowPlayerWh: (Experimental) Should we show player pawn when riding the wildlife
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.EnergyConsum: Defines the amount of Energy consumed when the associated functions are called
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.EnergyRestor: Defines the amount of Energy restored when the associated functions are called
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.BiomeVariant: Defines the color variant for each biome. Chicken, Boar and Wolf now have different color variants to use.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Despawn.Descrip: Despawns any existing Wildlife spawned from this device on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Despawn.Desc: Despawns any existing Wildlife spawned from this device.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Destroy Spawner: Destroy this spawner on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.AggressionLe: Determines how aggressive Wildlife will be when in combat with a target. This will affect values on the Wildlife such as attack cooldowns and chances to do certain attacks. Default leaves the Wildlife at their base level of aggression based on the type. Hive Swarmers default to Very High and Hive Lobbers default to Low.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ChangePatrol:
Determines how often the spawner will select a new random Patrol Path within its Patrol Path Group.
If NEVER, the device will always use the first Patrol Path in the Patrol Path Group.
Determines if Wildlife are able to drop resources on elimination.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.CanAssignToD:
Determines if Wildlife can be assigned patrol paths that are disabled to use in the future. 
If OFF, disabled paths will be ignored unless all paths are disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.SpawnOnTimer: Determines if Wildlife should be spawned on a timer, or only when receiving events.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Taming.Descr: Determines if Wildlife spawned by this device are able to be tamed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Invincible.D: Determines if Wildlife spawned from this device can take damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Riding.Descr: Determines if the Wildlife spawned by this device can be ridden or not. Currently only Wolf, Boar and Raptor are supported.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.AllowRidingO: Determines if the Wildlife spawned by this device can only be ridden by the players in the same team or not.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ShouldRandom:
Determines if the device should randomly select a path to use.
If OFF, the device will select the path (in order of their indexes if they have been set) that has not had a Wildlife spawned on it, which resets after a Wildlife has spawned on each Patrol Path in the Patrol Group.
NOTE: If multiple paths have the same index they will be randomly ordered between themselves.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.bPreventPlay: Determines if the player is allowed to dismount by pressing an input key
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.EnableResumi:
Determines if the wildlife should resume patrolling their path if it was disabled and then enabled.
If OFF, the wildlife must be assigned a path through a path's "Assign AI To Path" function to continue path following.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ActivateFrom: Determines if this device requires that a player be within a specified distance in order to spawn Wildlife.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.AllowInfinit: Determines if this device should restrict the maximum number of Wildlife spawned in its lifetime.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ForceSpawn.D: Determines if this device should spawn new Wildlife when it is at its Spawn Count cap. When new Wildlife are spawned in this way, the oldest Wildlife from this device is eliminated.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.bAllowSameTy: Determines if wildlife of the same type can attack each other while on different teams.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.WildlifeTeam: Determines in which Team the Wildlife will be assigned to, can specify a Team Index when needed
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ChangePatrol: Determines the amount of time of new spawned Wildlife will be selecting the Patrol Path. After it ends, new spawned Wildlife will randomly select Patrol Paths. This won't impact Wildlife that have been spawned already.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.MaximumTamed: Determines the limit of Wildlife from this device that a player can tame in game. Default means applying the same option set in the island settings. The tame limit on device won't be larger than the island setting limit.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.SpriteActiva: Determines the number of times a Sprite can be activated from a player's inventory.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.SpawnThrough: Determines whether Wildlife must spawn within line of sight of the spawner or if they can spawn behind obstructing walls.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.EnabledOnGam: Determines whether the spawner is already enabled when the game starts.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.WildlifeTeam: Determines which team the Wildlife is Spawned

UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Spawn.Descripti: Spawns one Wildlife from this device on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Spawn.Descri: Spawns one Wildlife from this device.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Tame.Descriptio: Tames Wildlife spawned by this device to the instigating Player on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Tame.Descrip: Tames Wildlife spawned by this device to the instigating Player.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Ride.Descriptio: Teleports and rides the closet available Wildlife spawned by the device to the instigating Player on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Ride.Descrip: Teleports and rides the closet available Wildlife spawned by the device to the instigating Player.
The distance from the device that Wildlife can peacefully roam. Wildlife may be pulled out of this range when fleeing, engaging in combat, or pursuing a goal. Wildlife pulled far enough outside of the Wander Range will not return.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.ActivationDi: The distance from the spawner that a Player must be within for Wildlife to begin spawning.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.TamedFollowD: The distance from the taming Player that Wildlife will try to remain while tamed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.SpawnRadius_: The maximum distance from the device that Wildlife can spawn.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Type.Descrip: The type of Wildlife that will be spawned by this device.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Eliminated B: Transmit a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife are eliminated by a predator.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Something Is: Transmit a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife eat a pickup such as a Shroom or Meat.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Damaged.Desc: Transmit a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife take damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Eliminated B: Transmit a signal on the selected channel when tamed Wildlife are eliminated by a Player on another team.
Transmit a signal on the selected channel when untamed Wildlife are eliminated by a Player.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Force Spawne: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife are force spawned, causing the oldest Wildlife to be eliminated.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Eliminated.D: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife from this device are eliminated.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Tamed.Descri: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife from this device are tamed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Untamed.Desc: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife from this device are untamed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Dismounted.D: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife spawned from this device are dismounted.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Ridden.Descr: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when Wildlife spawned from this device are ridden.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.On Spawned.Desc: Transmits a signal on the selected channel when this device spawns Wildlife.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Untame From: Untames Wildlife spawned by this device that were tamed by the instigating Player.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Untame From Ins: Untames Wildlife spawned by this device, that were tamed by the instigating Player, on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_C.Untame All.Desc: Untames all Wildlife spawned by this device on receiving a signal from the selected channel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.Untame All.D: Untames all Wildlife spawned by this device.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_WildlifeSpawner_V2_C.SpawnOnPatro: Will spawn Wildlife on the selected Patrol Path Group.
